ANTHRAX, HUMAN, BOVINE - UGANDA: (WESTERN REGION)
*****************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Sun 6 Nov 2011
From: Gyaviira Makanga <gmakanga@yahoo.com> [edited]


I am a medical doctor working as a physician in Uganda.

There is an outbreak of anthrax in a human settlement in one of the
Western districts of the country at a location called Sheema
[district]. It is thought to have spread from cattle to humans through
ingestion of contaminated beef.

It is not clear how many people are affected, but there is a ban on
consuming beef and milk products and especially today 6 Nov 2011,
which was IDD [Eid] day for the Muslims, whose theme was the slaughter
of animals.

The Ministry of Agriculture is doing everything to control the
situation.

--
Dr Gyaviira Makanga
Physician
Uganda
<gmakanga@yahoo.com>

[Our thanks to Dr Makanga for this report. It is such active awareness
by our members that makes ProMED-mail stand out. We are very
appreciative. - Mod.MHJ]

