[2]
Date: Mon 7 Nov 2011
Source: Uganda News Picks [edited]
http://www.ugandapicks.com/2011/11/anthrax-kills-2-in-sheema-district.html


District health officials have disclosed that 2 people have died in
Sheema district following an outbreak of anthrax. The district health
officer, Dr Johnson Kabwishwa, said the disease reportedly broke out
in Mashojwa village in Muzira sub-county on 25 Oct 2011.

Kabwishwa identified the deceased as a 55-year-old butcher and another
man. The trio reportedly skinned a carcass of a cow. Kabwishwa said
the 2 men died last week [week of 31 Oct 2011] after they showed signs
similar to those of anthrax.

Kabwishwa also noted that 5 other people were admitted to Kabwohe
health Center IV with signs of the disease. He said most of the
residents who ate the meat were given antibiotic drugs.

